{"type":"message","id":"875f3187","parentId":"15d6e65c","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:25:09.740Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture. The current version is **2026.3.13**, but the document is dated **2026.4.14**. The document describes features that may not exist in the current codebase yet.\n\nLet me now check what's actually supposed to be running by looking at the full v2026.4.14 document more carefully to understand what should be activated.\n\nKey findings:\n- Current version: 2026.3.13\n- Document version: 2026.4.14 (newer than running code!)\n- The document likely describes planned features\n\nLet me now create a comprehensive plan based on what's actually feasible to activate right now. Let me check what the actual missing pieces are:\n1. The document mentions 3100 as gateway port, but 18789 is the actual gateway - this is a config difference\n2. The document mentions many services (3102, 3104, 3108) that may be from a different architecture\n3. Many features like Active Memory, Context Engine, Lobster Workflow may be plugins or future features\n\nLet me check what's available in the skills that might activate some of these features.","thinkingSignature":"0e0ccc31b17d49a69de3de17811914ddc506172905c4dfb9ab58c79850942078"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ou8yj3wse05x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there are more services that should be running\ncurl -s http://localhost:3106/ 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Check if 3100 and 3001 are bound to openclaw-related processes\nlsof -i :3100 2>/dev/null | head -5 || echo \"lsof not available\"\necho \"---\"\n# Check the openclaw config for port settings\ncat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in d.items() if 'port' in str(v).lower() or 'listen' in str(v).lower()}, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minima